The paper deals with the problem of estimating the popularity of personal names in a large population, which is relevant to several areas such as record linkage, database management, and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deal with natural language processing and text analysis. The paper also discusses statistical modeling and evaluation, which could fit into cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) categories.
